nk I read somewhere that Mamuro Oshii (the director) didn't think they would fit the movie.  Which I can understand if one would think of them like Jar-Jar.  Comic relief wouldn't exactly be very fitting for the overall gloomy sense of the movie.<br>
Oshii asked Shirow if he could make the movie the way he did, and Shirow okayed it.  The movie has all these religious things in it, which wasn't in the movie either, partially due to the fact that Oshii reads the Bible for philosophical (not religious) reasons.  The quote &quot;What we see now is like a dim image in a mirror..&quot; is almost exactly out of the bible.  I don't know what book/verse, but I can ask a friend of mine, cause he showed it to me once before.<br>
